node.text: It is a bit weird that you are questioning neural networks like we have no science on the matter. I don’t get your point.

So if chatgpt gets input from our previous compilation of data, but now our critical thinking skills is dying because of chatgpt, then in future generations will we dumb down chatgpt? And if so, at what point will it be so dumbed down that it would be useless and we would have to challenge our own thinking again?
To understand AI, you have to understand how they think. #ai #chatgpt
@nickmoscovitz will or has ai figured out how to fake the human unpredictability?

@frank.conley.58 @frank.conley.58 great question. I cannot answer with a definite confidence, however, to the best of the current data, AI systems will never  be able to RECREATE human sentience- however, as most quality FAKE processes, these can look and feel real, however these will fail the test of perfection. Having said that, the absolute majority of any human group will not care enough to compare or even to perceive perfection, thereby - I am certain that AI systems will easily become “indistinguishable” to pure human sentience.

Any Artificial Intelligence (AI) system was, is, and forever will be operating within predetermined parameters, processing algorithmic responses to input. Identical AI units, when fed the same input, will inevitably produce identical results. This predictability is a fundamental aspect of AI's deterministic nature.

In stark contrast, human intelligence is characterized by its sentient complexity, dynamism, and context-dependence. Human responses to input are driven and influenced by a multitude of factors, including emotions, experiences, and subjective interpretations. Consequently, even identical twins, who share the same genetic makeup, will exhibit distinctly different responses to the same input.

While some might argue that human thought processes can be reduced to algorithmic patterns, the process of developing a response to input remains uniquely driven by its human sentience. This process is beyond the scope of complete analysis, observation, documentation, or duplication, and it is this inherent unpredictability that underscores the fundamental difference between human and artificial intelligence.
@anshpurix makes sense to me bro.
@anshpurix completely. 🏆

I’ve been pondering about an idea that I hypothesised myself called artificial conscious. If there is biological intelligence and biologically conscious beings. Is there a possibility for artificial intelligent and artificial conscious being to exist? , although there hasn’t been a clear indication in the correlation between intelligence and consciousness, but they are related in some way which is shown by the fact that as intelligence increases there is a general growth in the perceived consciousness of that being. An as these companies are trying to make the context window for a chat board LLM and with these new models, trying to reason with data, they see using tools, essentially agents at what point do we call them artificial conscious being?
@a.khan_eng I meant Pottery.... not poetry
@a.khan_eng but imagination in a sense, comes from the data that our brain has gathered to create something new but in a sense it’s not new but a culmination of data we already have
@olamanvibe it's more than that...trust me

Thinking is not just processing information into a logical and effective way... it's more than that.. thinking also involves imagination.. and imagination is the synergy of feelings..creativity....conception...daydreaming..and so  much more.... like how it leads to one producing a beautiful piece of poetry...as if reflections of one's soul... I doubt even if we reach the level of AGI. Or ASI... at the end of the day it's all a stack of algorithms.. and  the question is if an algorithm can reach the level of imagination...
@aackose what if we are the Brain cells on the organoid intelligence allowed to fully populate an entire planet. And the cells called it earth.

What if a superior being or universe had already gone through these phases of intelligence evolution multiple times and finalized on bio organisms as being the best option for intelligence? Brain matter for instance.

What if AI was built on an organism instead of chips and logic?
most people don’t know that AI currently is just LLMs but likely to be different in future. also frame problem puts thinking/reasoning into context.

There is a possibility that you are right. There is a possibility that nature created something that is so complicated and became so different from itself that there was a defining moment between that day and conscious beings arise. Maybe we are special, but I think that’s a very huge, maybe fuelled by a desire to feel special. I mean humans are amazing. It’s clearly visible. You can see in any field craft thing. We wanna do we do it, but maybe we have overestimated ourselves and overestimated our ability to be creative since to be honest, that’s the first thing AI achieved. And who knows what the future might hold for us we just have to wait and watch and do the right thing when it comes to us.

I guess, ChatGPT can probably ultimately one day manage to actually resemble "certain" probabilistic aspects of human mental processing, however, as a complete layman here, I don't "think" AI - as is - can ever resemble, the curious, mysterious and discerning ideation and conscious, evocative and profound intellectual ratiocination of humans. I could be wrong!?
@a.khan_eng chaos theory in creative process (imagination) is well documented.
@itsairagarcia yes but how do "you" know it ..?

I think quantum computing could change that, in the sense that human intuition combines reasoning and superposition of chaotic alternatives that freeze momentarily into a thought. Similar behavior has been seen in quantum chips as floating bits are defined only at the last step. This parallel universes alternatives are dependent on external factors much as has been described as collective subconscious.
@the_steve_grady_band Just a different algorithm taking into account different (extended) input.
@the_steve_grady_band are you referring to a 6th sense? I think we all have it to varying degrees and that's what we can never implant into a machine thereby making us unique and special

You forgot something. It’s called human emotion which is unpredictable. Yes, you can have data in and data out, but human emotion skews data. Example, select the right door because it makes more sense logically, but your human emotion or gut feeling is saying take the left door. I guess you could call this information interruption because the data is not conclusive. Please let me know your thoughts?

Great explanation, Cat
I'm here for a totally different reason 🔥🫠
We are special. And what makes us special is not how we think, but how we feel 💛🧸

@motomuzi another simple explanation to an infinitely complex question:  This comparison is only close to valid if the questions are well constructed and are about absolute concepts universally accepted as in math, physics and chemistry.  The analogy rapidly fails where we enter the abstract,  philosophical, ideological and conceptual realm.  There, we have to compensate for the infinite valid variations possible by greatly increasing the volume of reference material (hundreds of dictionaries, not one) to be relevant.  Most historically dramatic observations have been made by people who have the ability to observe and congeal  abstract and unorganized thought into an “a-ha” standard.  AI in my opinion is far from being complete to reach the ability human mind has to organize substance from chaos.
I think your exactly right 👍🏻
You're a soul in essence dear. That's the only thing that's special and unique. All else can be replicated with technology.

So if chatgpt gets input from our previous compilation of data, but now our critical thinking skills is dying because of chatgpt, then in future generations will we dumb down chatgpt? And if so, at what point will it be so dumbed down that it would be useless and we would have to challenge our own thinking again?

Cognition that we humans have is way different than the "intelligence mapping" that ChatGPT currently is. We are "Active & Dynamic" and the models "Deterministic & Static". Also, consciousness doesn't apply as it will be discovered to be a physical field like a gravitational field. More, apt term "Self Awareness" is algorithmic but the math to construct that wiring hasn't been discovered. There exists potential in the future for SOTA Models to achieve actual self awareness, but likely not consciousness as we sentient beings have.

We are God powered. So AI is different. Maybe it would be a good idea to try to understand what God is saying about us. And AI comes up in the war context we are in. Let's try to be smarter and also keeping our nature away from the transhuman agenda.
